parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become extremely difficult to turn or lock up, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering alert light flashes or remains on
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
and the "Check Power Steering System" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Hardness and Failure in Cold Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal becomes hard or unresponsive in cold weather, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard or solid
the brake pedal does not respond or feels spongy
the vehicle does not stop or slows down slowly
the ABS system grinds or makes unusual noises
the brake pedal feels wooden or frozen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag system indicator light is on
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of a crash
the airbag system is faulty or malfunctioning.
